definition.value: A coloboma of the ciliary body.
Any structural anomaly of a cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.
A reduction in the numbers of pro-B cells (defined by coexpression of CD34 and CD19). Earlier B-cell precursors are defined by expressing surface CD34 and cytoplasmic TdT in the absence of CD19.

label.value: Anti-granulocyte-macrophage colony stimulating factor antibody positivity

definition.value: Any functional abnormality of erythrocytes (red-blood cells).
Any deviation from the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.
An abnormal elevation above the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.
An abnormal reduction below the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of hemoglobin in the blood.
An abnormal reduction below normal hemoglobin concentration in the circulation.
